Author: zatJUM#9924
Content: A question about barterdex: let's say I want to sell 1 BTC against KMD. I send 1 BTC, 1.2 BTC and 1/777 BTC so I have 3 UTXOs. If I place my order to sell 1 BTC, "Max UTXO size" will not show "1" as I could expect, but the equivalent in KMD (5k KMD more or less, depending of the price I want to sell my BTC for KMD).

Author: cipi#4502
Content: if you place a BTC/KMD ask, the values are shown in KMD, so a potential buyer (using KMD) knows which value he could use in the buy-call

Author: zatJUM#9924
Content: yes, but perhaps he could also knows he wants to "buy 1 BTC", rather than "spend 5000 KMD"

Author: cipi#4502
Content: yes, but the buy call takes relvolume as parameter, like this: `curl --url "http://127.0.0.1:7783" --data "{\"userpass\":\"$userpass\",\"method\":\"buy\",\"base\":\"OOT\",\"rel\":\"KMD\",\"relvolume\":1,\"price\":0.03}"`

Author: cipi#4502
Content: so if i want to know what relvolume i could pass, so that the buy-call works, i need this value
